HEADWORD: Isocyanuric
<hw>I`so*cy`a*nu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + <ets>cyanuric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Designating, or pertaining to, an acid isomeric with cyanuric acid,
and called also <altname>fulminuric</altname> <it>acid</it>. See under
<er>Fulminuric</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

